annotation.TEXT: Argh, once again, I didn't think to pause the game during the "Hurry up!" sound effect!
Actually, I'm probably not going to bother trying to destroy every single brick. That would take way too long. So, I'll just destroy most of the bricks.
Looks like Rumia's using her powers of darkness on everything but her hair.

...I'm back at the very beginning! So, I think this hack must have some special ASM or something, which disables the midpoint flag when you Start+Select out of a level, meaning midpoints will only function if you leave by dying. Alright, voting results time!
So, the other enemies around here use 8-bit SMB1 graphics as well. Why not go totally 8-bit with all the graphics, though?
It's also neither flammable nor inflammable.
Also, there are Torpedo Teds. Well, these skull-and-crossbones boxes have to be more than just decoration, right?
Oh, was that Rumia?
Yeah, I thought I remembered that this level was SMB1-themed! But, why is it in the water on the map, and why does it have "Ocean" in its name?
Bah, only 30. Well, I definitely made a good effort there, that's for sure.
Gotta check every pipe...
There's the goal. Also, I think this is a blatant Vanilla Dome 2 edit.
Okay, so I guess the red Lava Lotuses eat things whole. I bet they're instant death if I touch one of them and get eaten.
If you get a star, you can run free within society! That's why YOU'RE the star! - By those eagerly awaiting the comeback of the Southern All Stars [Japanese pop band...?]

(And then after several failures, you decide to try a regular Poké Ball or a Great Ball for whatever reason, and that actually works, where your more powerful balls had failed. I've had that happen so many times in the older Pokémon games. Silly RNG.)
Since I'm not going to hit every single brick, if it turns out I missed something that was hidden in one or more of them, let me know.
Okay, so is there a star in this level?
37-life combo!
Ah, here's the "Ocean" that was advertised. Maybe this level's name should've been "Classic Cave and Ocean (Easy)".
Man, I have a feeling that the cape is going to utterly break this level. But then again, the cape is cape-able (heh) of utterly breaking a lot of levels.
Goal tape average so far: 280 / 8 = 35 stars each.
That opened up a path to the Blue Switch Palace, which could be handy if you want to return to world 1 this way for some reason.
Alright, time for me to be the star!
DOUBLE KILL!
Yes! I have no idea how, but that crazy plan somehow worked!
Alright, so You're the Star! won! However, I feel like doing things differently today for no real reason. I'm going to play Classic Ocean (Easy) 1st, and then You're the Star! 2nd.
Hello, and welcome back to Scarlet Devil Mario! Now, before I get to the voting results, I'm going to revisit Crystal Cave (Normal) just to show something. Let me quickly get to midpoint...
BGM: Super Mario Bros. - Underwater
Whoa, that's a lot of bricks. Once again, I'm not going to break them all, but I'll smash most of them.
"Is that sooo?"

Zwee!
So much cutoff!
Okay, now it's You're the Star!'s turn to be the star!
Goal tape average so far: 250 / 7 = 35.714 stars each.
My OCD must be on vacation or something right now, because I'm just not concerned with collecting every last coin here. However, I do kinda want that 1-up, since it seems to be challenging me...
BGM: Kirby 64: The Crystal Shards - Adeleine Battle Theme
Ah, there was a Yoshi coin there. Cool.
Yep, those foreground fish are frozen alright.
BGM: Super Mario Bros. - Underground

Okay, if I Start+Select out now, and then immediately reenter the level...
Can't be cape-thwacked, but the cape does work on its shots.
Fireballs might be more useful here. Plus, I want to try for a double kill.
Gray Spinies? Are those Buzzy Beetles in disguise?
Aw, only 30?
And there's the goal! Well, clearly this is a bonus level that's meant for life-farming purposes, which is nice. Okay, now how can I aim for the top of the goal?
There's the last Yoshi coin, and I'm guessing the goal is just on the other side of this pipe.
I'm intentionally skipping the flower and the Yoshi along the way so that my current status remains the same.
See ya, cloud!
That opened up a path to this ghost house up here.
The bottom and top of the screen are a floor and ceiling respectively, so no trying any funny out-of-bounds business here.
This is so risky...
Huh, the custom star music is playing, even though this level used the vanilla SMW music "Here We Go!".
Ahh! There's cutoff! Here's the obligatory joke about how this hack's not gonna be accepted at SMW Central!
This sea is inhabited by the rare but deadly Jelectros and Lava Lotuses. Be careful! And after hitting this message block, the small foreground fish will freeze in place. "Is that sooo?"
Okay, now remember how last time, the midpoint in Crystal Cave (Easy) didn't work when I Start+Selected out of the level, but this one here in Crystal Cave (Normal) did work after I died later on?
Lives just maxed out there.
Now, normally I find flying Cheepos to be a pain, but not when I'm the star!
Huh, I wonder why the bottom Lava Lotus there spits out different kinds of fireballs than usual? Anyway, let's see if I can get this 1-up without getting hurt. I have a plan...
So, where should I head next? Swimsuit Mania/Edition (Normal), or Dark Ghost House (Easy)? Place your votes now! To be continued... Ze!
..."Gulp"? Did that Lava Lotus just eat that Torpedo?
I'll remember to one of these days...
Umm... screw it. I'm not gonna waste time with those upside-down pipes. Of course, if any of them are actually enterable, let me know.
MULTI KILL!
Also, the Goombas had NES graphics, but the pipe, blocks, and ground seem to be from All-Stars.
BTW, I tested this on my other file, and if you go this way without first unlocking any of the Normal levels in world 1 the usual way, you can actually reach Hakurei Shrine 2 (Normal) this way.
Hey there, fishin' Lakitu! That's for the 1-up! Now, BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! WOO! TRI-FORMATION!

Alright, which world am I warping to here? (Aw, I should've put the Super Meat Boy "WAAAARP ZOOOONE!!!" sound clip into the video here. I only just thought of that now, while annotating.)

Oh, come on. That 1-up really doesn't want to be caught, just like certain Pokémon. You know the ones, where you toss so many Ultra/Dusk/Timer/Whatever Balls while they're sleeping/paralyzed and in the red for health, and they still won't get captured.
However, they don't move, and they're not spitting projectiles at me, so even with the risk of instant-death, I think they're not as nasty as their green counterparts.
Also, there's a bubbled Bob-omb.
Well, there's bubbled Goombas.
Yes, let's destroy ALL of the bricks!!! Mwahaha!!!
Why are there a few water tiles up here? I wouldn't exactly call this an "Ocean"...
Also, I can scroll backwards (some SMB1-styled levels in other hacks prevent backwards scrolling), and the Fire Flower still has its SMW graphics.
Okay, I saw a purple coin at the top of the screen there, which makes me suspicious.
Star chain: 2
